// XOR cancels equal pairs (a ^ a = 0; a ^ 0 = a), leaving only the unique element.
public int SingleNumber(int[] nums) {
    int x = 0;
    foreach (int n in nums) x ^= n;
    return x;
}
```
**Complexity:** O(n) time, O(1) space — the O(1)-space answer they want (no hashmap).

